      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo i just finished replacing the brake pads on my 2018 camry but now when i test drive it i get this really high pitched squealing noise when i hit the brakes. not sure if it's a worn sensor or maybe a stuck caliper? any idea what i should check first?",
