      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Given the inconsistent retraction and the piercing \"scream\" during braking, an issue within the caliper assembly or brake rotor is very likely. This sudden noise could indicate rotor run-out or a component internally binding within the caliper, which needs careful inspection. It would be best to have a qualified technician inspect the caliper slide pins and the rotor surface for warping before assuming a full assembly failure.",
      "source": "target",
